  "decision_conditions": [
    "<p>The proposal, by reason of its location immediately outside the trading area of Ridley Road Market, and the lack of identified suitable access for construction vehicles and the submission of a framework construction, management and logistics plan, could obstruct and restrict the operation of the market, to the detriment of the vitality of Ridley Road Market and Dalston Town Centre.&nbsp;As such the proposal is contrary to policies SD6 (Town centres and high streets), D13 (Agent of Change), E9 (Retail, markets and hot food takeaways) and T4 (Assessing and mitigating transport impacts) of the London Plan 2021 and policies PP2 (Dalston), LP32 (Town Centres), LP33 (Hackney Central and Dalston), LP40 (Street Markets) and LP43 (Transport and Development) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.<br></p>",
    "<p>The proposal, by reason of its height and location due south of the outdoor learning space at Colvestone Primary School, would result in undue loss of light and loss of outlook/increased sense of enclosure to that outdoor area, to the detriment of the utility of the space and the learning experience that is offered. As such the proposal is contrary to policies D4 (Delivering good design), D5 (Inclusive design) and S3 (Education and childcare facilities) of the London Plan 2021 and policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP2 (Development and Amenity) and LP8 (Social and Community Infrastructure) of the Hackney Local Plan 2020.<br></p>"
  ],
